Title : Samuel Silva
Text : <!-- Do not remove this line! -->
'''Samuel Silva''' (born 1983)<ref>[http://www.travelerstoday.com/articles/2813/20120823/samuel,silva,creates,extraordinary,art,using,only,ballpoint,pens,photos.htm "Samuel Silva Creates Extraordinary Art Using Only Ballpoint Pens (PHOTOS)"]. ''Travelers Today'', Aug 23, 2012</ref> is a lawyer from Portugal whose [[Ballpoint pen artwork|ball point pen drawings]] received "viral" recognition in 2012. He lives and works in the United Kingdom. <ref name=sa>[http://www.scientificamerican.com/article/artists-play-with-light-shadown-trick-the-eye/?page=8 " Artists Play With Light and Shadows to Trick the Eye"]. ''Scientific American'' Feb 14, 2013 |By Susana Martinez-Conde and Stephen L. Macknik </ref><ref>[http://www.thisiscolossal.com/2012/08/amazing-portrait-drawn-with-ballpoint-pens-by-samuel-silva/ "This is Not a Photograph: Amazing Portrait Drawn with Ballpoint Pens by Samuel Silva"]. ''This is Colossal'', by Christopher Jobson on August 22, 2012</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url = https://www.mirror.co.uk/news/weird-news/samuel-silva-pen-pictures-amazing-3393158|title = Amazing artist creates lifelike drawings with ballpoint pens|last = |first = |date = |work = |access-date = 23 February 2015|publisher = Mirror UK}}</ref>

==Early life and education==

Silva was born in Portugal,<ref name=tfp>[http://www.toledofreepress.com/2013/05/01/the-pen-is-mightier-artists-ink-drawings-resemble-photographs/ "The pen is mightier: Artist’s ink drawings resemble photographs"]. ''Toledo Free Press'', Written by Jeff McGinnis </ref> and started drawing at the age of two, He continued to draw throughout his childhood and teenage years. He attended Law School<ref>[http://www.lostateminor.com/2014/02/22/interview-ballpoint-pen-hyper-realism-artist-samuel-silva/ "Interview with ballpoint pen hyper-realism artist Samuel Silva"]. ''LoState Minor''/ Inigo del Castillo in New Illustration on 22 February 2014</ref> and has been practicing law since 2007.<ref>[http://www.theportugalnews.com/news/portuguese-lawyer-takes-world-by-storm-with-brilliant-biro-masterpieces/26688 "Portuguese lawyer takes world by storm with brilliant biro masterpieces"]. ''The Portugal News'', by Carrie-Marie Bratley, in News · 30-08-2012</ref>  He has no formal art training.

==Career==

Silva began posting scans of his drawings on the website Deviant Art.<ref>[http://www.heraldsun.com.au/news/world/amazingly-this-is-a-drawing-made-with-ballpoint-pens-not-a-photograph/story-fnd134gw-1226456675564 "Amazingly, this is a drawing made with ballpoint pens, not a photograph"]. ''Herald Sun''   Simon Crerar, News Corp Australia Network     August 23, 2012 </ref> In 2012 his realistic art<ref>[http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2012/08/23/samuel-silvas-amazing-pho_n_1822572.html "Artist Samuel Silva's Incredible Photorealistic Ballpoint Pen Drawings (PHOTOS)"]. ''The Huffington Post''  |  By Hallie Sekoff 08/23/2012</ref> created with ballpoint pens<ref>[https://www.mirror.co.uk/news/weird-news/samuel-silva-pen-pictures-amazing-3393158 " Pictured: Amazing artist creates lifelike drawings with ballpoint pens"] ''Mirror'',  9 April 2014 By Ben Burrows</ref> and received attention from a number of news outlets and magazines around the world, including the Toledo Free Press,<ref name=tfp /> the Huffington Post, the ''Herald'', and Scientific American. <ref name=sa></ref>

Silva's drawings are created with cross-hatching and minute detail, and are sometimes mistaken for photographs.<ref>[http://www.express.co.uk/news/uk/341802/Brilliant-Biro-doodles-are-perfect-for-any-picture "Brilliant Biro doodles are perfect for any picture"]. ''Express''. Rick Seniey.</ref> His drawings are recreations of existing photographs.

